TITLE: Implementing Graceful Shutdown for Telegraf Bots in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Code to ensure that Telegraf bots gracefully close connections before the process is terminated. This should be added to the end of the bot's entry file to handle SIGINT and SIGTERM signals properly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feathers-studio/telegraf-docs/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
process.once("SIGINT", () => bot.stop("SIGINT"));
process.once("SIGTERM", () => bot.stop("SIGTERM"));
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling Webhook Reply for Session Safety
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to disable webhookReply when using Telegraf in webhook mode to ensure session safety. This is a required configuration for webhook deployments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feathers-studio/telegraf-docs/blob/master/guide/session.md#2025-04-19_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
const bot = new Telegraf(token, { telegram: { webhookReply: false } })
```

