TITLE: Setting Up Environment Variables for Telegraf Bots in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Code for safely accessing environment variables needed for Telegraf bot configuration, including port, bot token, and webhook domain. This ensures secrets are not hardcoded and validates required parameters before bot initialization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feathers-studio/telegraf-docs/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// default to port 3000 if PORT is not set
const port = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;

// assert and refuse to start bot if token or webhookDomain is not passed
if (!process.env.BOT_TOKEN) throw new Error('"BOT_TOKEN" env var is required!');
if (!process.env.WEBHOOK_DOMAIN) throw new Error('"WEBHOOK_DOMAIN" env var is required!');
```

